      • getBestTasksMatches

        public java.util.List<java.lang.String> getBestTasksMatches(java.util.Map<java.lang.String,LinkedTaskAgileEntityInfo> candidateTasksInfo,
                                                            TimeSheetLineAgileEntityInfo timesheetLineAgileEntityInfo)
        This method will be invoked for each timesheet line by PPM if your ExternalWorkItem includes a TimeSheetLineAgileEntityInfo value.
        It is used to find out which PPM Task or Project should be autoamtically related with the timesheet line without user having to manually provide the information. Each Task of the PPM work plans that is linked using the same Connector instance and to the same projet ID will have its LinkedTaskAgileEntityInfo passed to this method, and it's the job of the connector to return the task IDs of the best matches, sorted from the best match to the worse.
        PPM will then pick the first task (or containing project) in the list against which the user can log time, and automatically relate it with the timesheet line.
        If this method returns null or an empty list, or if the user cannot log time against any of the returned tasks (or their project), then the line will not be automatically related with a PPM task or Project.

        It is not necessary (nor expected) that all task IDs from the map will be returned in the list ; you should only return a task ID if the Entity IDs in meta data indicate that you'll likely want to have this line costs be captured in the project.
        Default implementation looks for perfect match of metadata as top preference, and preference lowers as linked task metadata has more IDs that are null but are not null in timesheet metadata (means the linked agile data will be more generic as the timesheet line.)
        We expect every Agile Connector to override this behavior for proper auto-matching behavior.

        Parameters:
        candidateTasksInfo - a Map with task IDs as Keys and Agile entity metadata as values.
        timesheetLineAgileEntityInfo - Agile metadata of a timesheet line.
        Returns:
        An ordered list of the task IDs (keys of parameter candidateTasksInfo) from the most to the least preferred candidate for auto-matching the line.
